parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatback bolts can cause the seat to collapse or recline excessively, leading to a loss of back support and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seatback leans too far back
the driver is in a reclined position
the driver has no back support

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers may or may not work
stopping and starting for no apparent reason
or failing to operate during rain or snow.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Alternator Failure and Electrical System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause a loss of electrical power, leading to malfunctioning of critical systems, and in some cases, a fire, which can result in a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Dashboard lights and meters flashing and moving wildly
broken positive terminal post of the battery.
